We just want to tell you congratulations on accepting Jesus Christ and what kind of wonderful decision you've made.

02:41:00.153 --> 02:41:06.118
We want to love on you. Thank you for being here. And if you said that prayer tonight, welcome to the family.

02:41:06.119 --> 02:41:11.017
To you that have been backsliding and not been living right, welcome back home.

02:41:11.018 --> 02:41:16.361
We're not here to judge you and beat you down. We're just here to love you and to say, 'Welcome home, soldier.

02:41:16.362 --> 02:41:24.202
Welcome home, daughter. Welcome home, son. We're excited you came back home.'Jesus has never left you and never forsook you.

02:41:24.203 --> 02:41:28.559
He's always been there with his arms wide open, just loving on you.

02:41:28.560 --> 02:41:33.939
He's an ever-present help in a time of need. He's always been there, and he's always loving on you.

02:41:33.940 --> 02:41:39.682
He's always looking. He saved the best for last. And you've come to the kingdom for such a time as this.

02:41:39.683 --> 02:41:45.330
Even tonight, in the middle of the night, you've come to the kingdom for such a time as this.

02:41:45.331 --> 02:41:49.592
'Welcome home, son, daughter.'That's what he's saying. Isn't that wonderful?

02:41:49.593 --> 02:41:59.154
I don't know if anybody said the prayer tonight, but Braden, doing the math—we did it really quick for you—sixteen of you did it.

02:41:59.155 --> 02:42:03.780
So all sixteen of you, welcome home. That's wonderful. Welcome home.

02:42:03.781 --> 02:42:09.276
I'm excited you all said the prayer tonight with us. Isn't Jesus wonderful?

02:42:09.277 --> 02:42:16.686
Well, as we close now, thank you for being with us. It's Wednesday night, late tonight.

02:42:16.687 --> 02:42:21.295
Now it's already Thursday. We'll be back again to pray with y'all some more.

02:42:21.296 --> 02:42:24.575
We're so thankful for your time. Thank you for being with us.

02:42:24.576 --> 02:42:30.816
We pray you were richly blessed and you're stirred up in your spirit, excited, and Jesus Christ is coming.

02:42:30.817 --> 02:42:37.717
I'm excited. I'm glad I showed up. So, we'll go over this book next time, I believe.

02:42:37.718 --> 02:42:42.945
Maybe if I pull Diana away from her other duties and have her come over and read to me, I love it when she's able to.

02:42:42.946 --> 02:42:49.896
She's so busy. You all pray for Diana. She needs strength. She works her tail feathers off.

02:42:49.897 --> 02:42:58.197
I told her, I said, 'Baby, I've never seen somebody work as hard as you do.'But, very thankful for her and even being able to spend time with me tonight.

02:42:58.198 --> 02:43:03.062
So thankful. I'm excited when you come. I got my girlfriend with me.

02:43:03.063 --> 02:43:12.234
So, I love you all. We love you. Remember, put a smile on your face and a song in your heart.

02:43:12.235 --> 02:43:20.478
Jesus loves you and we love you. God bless you and we'll see you again soon. Bye-bye.

